1954;;Isn't Life Wonderful!;;British;;Harold French;;Cecil Parker, Eileen Herlie;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isn%27t_Life_Wonderful!;;In Edwardian England, alcoholic Uncle Willie (Donald Wolfit) is an embarrassment to his family. Head of the household father (Cecil Parker), decides to set Willie up as the manager of a bicycle shop, hoping to impress visiting American heiress Virginia van Stuyden (Dianne Foster). The surprise for everyone comes when Uncle Willie's little shop begins to prosper.